definitions.definition: The art or sport of duelling with swords , especially with the 17th- to 18th-century European dueling swords and the practice weapons descended from them ( sport fencing ).
Material used to make fences , fences used as barriers or an enclosure.
examples: Fencing was erected around the field to keep the horses in.

definitions.definition: Receiving and  buying of stolen goods.
